<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,556,188,215]" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">
Description. Female 
<typeStatus box="[446,551,189,215]" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Yellow spiders of medium size (
<figureCitation box="[923,1007,188,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,387,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,381,1931]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Minosiella apolakia sp.n. 23 Holotype habitus, dorsal view. 24 Same, ventral view. 25 Paratype, epigyne. 26 Paratype, vulva." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351036/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">Figs 23</figureCitation>
─24). Legs same color of body except for Ta and Mt which are slightly darker than the rest of leg segments. Measurements: TL 5.148; CL 2.297; CW 1.654; AL 2.539. Eye sizes and interdistances: 
<collectionCode box="[672,734,261,287]" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">AME</collectionCode>
0.120, PME 0.089x0.071, PLE 0.129, ALE 0.117, AME-AME 0.075 (
<emphasis box="[232,258,297,322]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">ca</emphasis>
by 1/2 their diameter), AME-ALE almost touching, PME-PLE 0.060 (
<emphasis box="[1069,1095,297,322]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">ca</emphasis>
by 1/2 their diameter), PME- PME 0.074 (
<emphasis box="[300,326,333,358]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">ca</emphasis>
by PME width). All eyes pearly white with black surroundings, especially 
<collectionCode box="[1193,1259,333,359]" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">AME</collectionCode>
. PME oval and closer to PLE than to each other, all others round. PER straight, AER straight to slightly recurved. Prosoma with widening thoracic region, fovea at posterior half of its length. Labium and maxillae triangular, longer than wide. Chelicerae with 1 tooth on 
<collectingRegion box="[460,504,441,467]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">RM</collectingRegion>
and bifid serrated keel on 
<collectionCode box="[808,852,441,467]" country="USA" name="Pratt Museum" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">PM</collectionCode>
. Leg formula is IV&gt;I&gt;II&gt;III. Legs spination: Leg I: Fe 2d; leg II: Fe 2d; leg III: Fe 5d, Pa/Ti/Mt spinose; leg IV: Fe 6d, Ti/Mt spinose; palp: Fe 2d; Ti spinose. Femoral spines thinner, resembling long bristles. Pa III and IV densely setose dorsally, Ta not densely scopulated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">
Epigyne (
<figureCitation box="[262,352,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,387,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,381,1931]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Minosiella apolakia sp.n. 23 Holotype habitus, dorsal view. 24 Same, ventral view. 25 Paratype, epigyne. 26 Paratype, vulva." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351036/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">Figs 25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[366,398,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1518,1543]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,845,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,839,1451]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 27–28. Minosiella apolakia sp.n. paratype 27 Epigyne. 28 Vulva. g: glandular head, co: copulatory opening, Sc: scape." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351038/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">27</figureCitation>
). Shield like atrium with almost parallel lateral margins, forming two chambers of almost equal size and a small median depression. Length of atrium ca double its width. Scape slightly widened at its end. Copulatory openings located at posterior base of epigynal plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">
Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[281,367,656,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1950,1975]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,387,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,381,1931]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Minosiella apolakia sp.n. 23 Holotype habitus, dorsal view. 24 Same, ventral view. 25 Paratype, epigyne. 26 Paratype, vulva." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351036/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">Figs 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[379,411,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1518,1543]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,845,1440]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,839,1451]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 27–28. Minosiella apolakia sp.n. paratype 27 Epigyne. 28 Vulva. g: glandular head, co: copulatory opening, Sc: scape." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3351038/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="446">28</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae coiled, forming bulging bean-like lateral chambers with glandular heads on posterior ends.
</paragraph>
